    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Analysis of Mutual Fund Schemes</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P.Appanasamy</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Mutual Fund Schemes</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5939</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The study conducted on the “Performance of Mutual fund schemes” of different Asset Management Companies, has revealed that funds which show high returns in any given year may not be considered to be the best performers. Likewise, funds which carry high risks may prove to be consistent in providing regular returns to its investors. The study also revealed that there are certain funds which reveal high returns per unit of risk undertaken by the investor. Also, choosing a mutual fund depends upon the sensitivity an investor has towards the market movements. Thus we find that the standard mutual fund indicators are relative measures and are not absolute, hence no fund can be accessed on the basis of any single parameter. All the indicators like beta, alpha, standard deviation, Sharpe ratio and R-squared, are intended to help investors determine the risk-reward profile of a mutual fund. The funds have to be assessed taking into consideration all the different parameters for selecting the best fund to be invested into. Choosing which fund is the best to invest in depends upon the market outlook of the investor and his risk-taking ability. Hence an apt fund would be the one, which matches the needs of its investor well and also is able to provide the investor with the returns desired by him.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/11412">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/11412</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
